Note: ========================================
Note: SQL Emitter
Note: ========================================
Note: Buffered SQL output for SQL generator
Note:
Note: Part of the Translation translation system - SQL backend
Note:
Note: This emitter provides efficient buffered output for SQL generation
Note: with support for keywords, identifiers, literals, and operators.
Note:
Note: Architecture:
Note:   - Exponentially growing buffer (4KB initial, 2x growth)
Note:   - Keyword emission (uppercase)
Note:   - Identifier emission (with quoting if needed)
Note:   - String literal emission (with proper escaping)
Note:   - Integer and float literal emission
Note:   - Operator emission
Note: ========================================

Import "stdlib/core/string.runa" as StringCore
Import "stdlib/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ========================================
Note: SQL Emitter Structure
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Emitter manages a growing buffer for SQL output, tracking
current position and buffer capacity. The buffer grows
exponentially (2x) when capacity is exceeded.
@End Reasoning

Type called "SQLEmitter":
    buffer as Integer         Note: Pointer to output buffer
    position as Integer       Note: Current write position in buffer
    capacity as Integer       Note: Total buffer capacity
End Type

Constant INITIAL_CAPACITY as Integer is 4096  Note: 4KB initial buffer

Process called "create_sql_emitter" returns Integer:
    Note: Create new SQL emitter with initial buffer

    Let emitter be proc allocate from Layout with 24

    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0, buffer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8, 0  Note: position = 0

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 16, INITIAL_CAPACITY  Note: capacity

    Return emitter
End Process

Process called "destroy_sql_emitter" takes emitter as Integer:
    Note: Destroy SQL emitter and free buffer

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0
    proc deallocate from Layout with buffer

    proc deallocate from Layout with emitter
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Buffer Management
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Ensure buffer has space for additional bytes. If not,
grow the buffer exponentially (2x current capacity).
@End Reasoning

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, additional_bytes as Integer:
    Note: Ensure buffer has space for additional bytes

    Let position be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 16

    Let needed_capacity be position plus additional_bytes

    If needed_capacity is less than or equal to capacity:
        Return  Note: Sufficient capacity
    End If

    Note: Calculate new capacity (exponential growth)
    Let new_capacity be capacity

    While new_capacity is less than needed_capacity:
        Set new_capacity to new_capacity multiplied by 2
    End While

    Note: Allocate new buffer
    Let new_buffer be proc allocate from Layout with new_capacity

    Note: Copy existing data to new buffer
    Let old_buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0
    proc copy_memory with old_buffer, new_buffer, position

    Note: Free old buffer
    proc deallocate from Layout with old_buffer

    Note: Update emitter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0, new_buffer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 16, new_capacity
End Process

Process called "copy_memory" takes source as Integer, dest as Integer, size as Integer:
    Note: Copy memory from source to destination

    Let i be 0

    While i is less than size:
        Let byte_value be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, i
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with dest, i, byte_value
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Character and String Emission
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Emit individual characters and strings to the buffer.
All emission goes through ensure_capacity to handle buffer growth.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer:
    Note: Emit single character (ASCII byte)

    proc ensure_capacity with emitter, 1

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0
    Let position be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8

    proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, char

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8, position plus 1
End Process

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, string as Integer:
    Note: Emit string to buffer

    Let string_len be proc string_length from StringCore with string

    proc ensure_capacity with emitter, string_len

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 0
    Let position be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8

    Note: Copy string bytes to buffer
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than string_len:
        Let char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with string, i
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position plus i, char
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with emitter, 8, position plus string_len
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: SQL Keyword Emission
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
SQL keywords should be emitted in uppercase for standard formatting.
This function converts keywords to uppercase before emission.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_keyword" takes emitter as Integer, keyword as Integer:
    Note: Emit SQL keyword in uppercase

    Let keyword_upper be proc to_uppercase from StringCore with keyword
    proc emit_string with emitter, keyword_upper
    proc deallocate from Layout with keyword_upper
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: SQL Identifier Emission
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Identifiers must be properly quoted if they contain special characters
or are SQL reserved keywords. This implementation checks each identifier
and applies double-quote quoting when necessary for SQL standard compliance.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_identifier" takes emitter as Integer, identifier as Integer:
    Note: Emit SQL identifier (with quoting if needed)

    Note: Check if identifier needs quoting
    Let needs_quoting be proc identifier_needs_quoting from identifier

    If needs_quoting is equal to 1:
        proc emit_char with emitter, 34  Note: " (double quote)
        proc emit_string with emitter, identifier
        proc emit_char with emitter, 34  Note: "
    Otherwise:
        proc emit_string with emitter, identifier
    End If
End Process

Process called "identifier_needs_quoting" takes identifier as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if identifier needs quoting
    Note: Identifiers need quoting if they contain spaces, special chars, or are keywords

    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with identifier

    If len is equal to 0:
        Return 1  Note: Empty identifier needs quoting
    End If

    Note: Check for spaces or special characters
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than len:
        Let char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with identifier, i

        Note: Check if character is alphanumeric or underscore
        Let is_alpha be 0

        Note: a-z
        If char is greater than or equal to 97:
            If char is less than or equal to 122:
                Set is_alpha to 1
            End If
        End If

        Note: A-Z
        If char is greater than or equal to 65:
            If char is less than or equal to 90:
                Set is_alpha to 1
            End If
        End If

        Note: 0-9 (not allowed as first character)
        If char is greater than or equal to 48:
            If char is less than or equal to 57:
                If i is greater than 0:
                    Set is_alpha to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Underscore
        If char is equal to 95:
            Set is_alpha to 1
        End If

        If is_alpha is equal to 0:
            Return 1  Note: Special character found, needs quoting
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Check if identifier is a SQL reserved keyword
    Note: SQL-92 and common extension keywords
    Let upper_id be proc string_to_uppercase from StringCore with identifier

    Note: Common SQL keywords (partial list - most frequently used)
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "SELECT" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "FROM" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "WHERE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "INSERT" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "UPDATE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "DELETE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "CREATE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "DROP" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "ALTER" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "TABLE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "INDEX" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "VIEW" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "JOIN" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "INNER" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with upper_id, "OUTER" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
